quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  9,55,"So let<sup>sg </sup>neither their wealths nor their children impress you. Indeed, Allah only wants to punish them thereby in the Earlier Life, and that their souls depart while they are deniers."
  9,56,"And they swear by Allah that they are most surely of you, but in no way are they of you<sup>pl </sup>; rather, they are a terrified people."
  9,57,"Were they to find a refuge or some caverns or any entrance, they would turn to it, rushing."
  9,58,"And of them is the one who criticizes you<sup>sg </sup>regarding donations. Yet if they{1}are given some of it, they are content; but if they are not given any of it, they are promptly angered.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from singular to plural.]
  9,59,"Yet if only they were content with what Allah and His Messenger had brought them and said, “Allah is sufficient for us; Allah will bring to us of His grace, as will His Messenger; indeed to Allah we turn wishfully.”"
  9,60,"Indeed, donations are only for the poor and the destitute<sup>pl </sup>and those who administer them and for those whose hearts are reconciled and for freeing slaves{1}and for the debt-ridden ones and in the way of Allah and for the homeless traveler—an obligation from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise.",footnotes:1:[Literally ‘necks’.]
  9,61,"And of them are those who hurt the Prophet and say, “He is just an ear.” Say<sup>sg </sup>, “An ear of goodness for you{1}. He has faith in Allah and he has faith in the believers and is a mercy{2}for those of you who have attained faith. And those who hurt the Messenger of Allah—for them is a painful punishment.",footnotes:1:[Meaning ‘listens for your own good’.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Hamza read it as: “…and in mercy for those of you…”]
